*sage-latex-2.3.1-r1 (12 Nov 2011)

  12 Nov 2011; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  -sage-latex-2.3.1.ebuild, +sage-latex-2.3.1-r1.ebuild,
  -files/sage-latex-2.3.1-chksum.patch,
  files/sage-latex-2.3.1-install-python-files-only.patch:
  switche to sage spkg for 2.3.1

  10 Nov 2011; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-latex-2.2.5-r2.ebuild, sage-latex-2.3.1.ebuild:
  Migrate to EAPI Migrate to EAPI 44

  06 Nov 2011; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  sage-latex-2.3.1.ebuild:
  fix S 

*sage-latex-2.3.1 (17 Jun 2011)

  17 Jun 2011; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  +sage-latex-2.3.1.ebuild, +files/sage-latex-2.3.1-chksum.patch,
  +files/sage-latex-2.3.1-install-python-files-only.patch:
  Revbump to 2.3.1. Switch to bitbucket sources, this requires generation of
  docs.

  14 Apr 2011; François Bissey <francois.bissey@canterbury.ac.nz>
  sage-latex-2.2.5-r2.ebuild:
  Make sage-latex support multiple python

  08 Sep 2010; François Bissey <f.r.bissey@massey.ac.nz> metadata.xml:
  Fix metadata

*sage-latex-2.2.5-r2 (03 Sep 2010)

  03 Sep 2010; François Bissey <f.r.bissey@massey.ac.nz>
  -sage-latex-2.2.5.ebuild, -sage-latex-2.2.5-r1.ebuild,
  +sage-latex-2.2.5-r2.ebuild:
  Remove most tex sources to avoid generating documentation, therefore
  requiring sage. Depend on pgf.

  02 Sep 2010; François Bissey <f.r.bissey@massey.ac.nz>
  +sage-latex-2.2.5.ebuild, +sage-latex-2.2.5-r1.ebuild,
  +files/sage-latex-2.2.5-install-python-files-only.patch, +metadata.xml:
  moved to dev-tex. Restore sage as a DEPEND until we sort out the doc.

  02 Sep 2010; François Bissey <f.r.bissey@massey.ac.nz>
  sage-latex-2.2.5-r1.ebuild:
  make sage a RDEPEND as it is not needed to install sage-latex, just to use
  it. It may help the circular dependency problem.

*sage-latex-2.2.5-r1 (08 Aug 2010)

